parameters:
\n<Ones>Rumahle is so vast. I got terribly lost just trying to get
out of town. And to think, my work only starts after I get
out and make it to the forest.
\n<Ones>Rui Let's go home together on the way back Okay
But it would be embarrassing if rumors started to spread

\n<Ones>Let's hold hands too (Ah, that's a relief. I was definitely
about to get lost.)

\n<Ones>What's that? But come to think of it, walking through the
noble district as twins might be a bit conspicuous. We might
get found out by our family. Guess I have no choice but to
memorize the way.

\n<Rui>The guards of Rumare don't come as far as the forest, huh.
It seems like they exterminate the monsters around the town,
but beyond here must be out of their jurisdiction.

\n<Rui>It's not threatening the town yet, but it might become
dangerous eventually. Taking care of monsters in such places
feels like it's within our adventurers' purview, doesn't it?

\n<Rui>But I mean, adventurer. It has a nice ring to it, doesn't
it? It feels romantic. Maybe girls don't understand? Fufufu

\n<Ones>I got lost at the forest exit... I'm glad Rui came...
*sniffle*.
The exit is in that direction.

\n<Ones>No way. I'll keep trying. After all, I'm saving up my
allowance to eat some Luma-R Chocolat.

\n<Ones>Hm...? Ah, that's right. I see, I remember seeing that tree!
Hmm hmm. Got it memorized.

\n<Rui>You shouldn't use trees as landmarks in the forest. Maybe
you should sharpen your claws instead?

\n<Rui>Ugh! This is bad... My, my stomach is starting to rumble...!
Ouch ouch ouch...

\n<Rui>The innkeeper gave me a cookie... It tasted awful and I spat
it out immediately, but it must have been poisoned or
something... That damn hag! She did it on purpose!

\n<Rui>It's not just that the old lady's cooking is bad. She's a
veritable poison factory, you know. I can't believe I even
tried it.

\n<Rui>She said her grandchild baked them, ahhhh!! And they were
wrapped so cutely tooooo!! Ahhhhh!! Sorry, I need a moment!
I'm going to fertilize the forest!

\n<Lintei>Hey Rui. Are you on forest cleaning duty? I've come to
survey the ecosystem.

\n<Lintei>Monsters prioritize attacking humans, but they don't live
solely on human flesh. They also feed on plants, deer, and
rabbits.

\n<Lintei>Understanding what kind of flora and fauna are in the
vicinity is very important for unraveling the breeding
mechanisms of monsters.

\n<Lintei>Whenever I take on a request from the nobles' district, I
make sure to buy some fine liquor to bring back. It's nice
to enjoy it myself, but it's really for the sake of my
companions.

\n<Lintei>The cheap alcohol everyone drinks doesn't exactly contain
healthy ingredients, you know. Collapsing from ruining your
health is not exactly becoming of an adventurer.
